'''''Beach Buggy Simulator''''' is a video game released for the [[ZX Spectrum]], [[Commodore 64]] and [[Amstrad CPC]] in [[1988 in video gaming|1988]].

==Gameplay==
[[image:Beach Buggy Simulator.png|thumb|left|ZX Spectrum screenshot]]
In ''Beach Buggy Simulator'', the players have to drive a beach buggy through several dune trials by jumping over the rocks and similar hazards, scattered along the way. The buggy is equipped with a gun for shooting down the helicopters that are passing by, trying to destroy the vehicle.<ref>{{Cite magazine|title=Games Update|url=https://archive.org/details/YourCommodoreIssue49Oct88/page/n17/mode/2up|magazine=[[Your Commodore]]|date=October 1988|access-date=2020-08-16|page=19|issue=49}}</ref> The goal is to reach the finish line before the time limit runs out.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Beach Buggy Simulator|first=Darran|last=Jones|url=https://www.retrogamer.net/retro_games80/beach-buggy-simulator/|website=[[Retro Gamer]]|date=2008-07-16|access-date=2020-08-16}}</ref>

